38:50.036 --> 38:51.204
| need to know
who she was.

38:52.205 --> 38:53.790
It fucks with you.

38:54.707 --> 38:57.669
Seeing someone who looks
almost exactly like you.

38:59.587 --> 39:00.463
How did you meet?

39:01.673 --> 39:03.049
[ CAR HORN BLARING ]

39:07.846 --> 39:09.347
[ FAINT SIREN BLARING ]

39:13.768 --> 39:15.228
No way! Lexie!

39:16.646 --> 39:18.606
It's Justin.

39:18.773 --> 39:22.485
We had a couple of seminars
together, in first year.

39:24.112 --> 39:25.238
Yeah.

39:26.990 --> 39:28.575
Of course, Justin.
Sorry.

39:28.741 --> 39:31.494
I- | heard your parents
put you in a rehab.

39:32.287 --> 39:33.162
That's rough.

39:34.789 --> 39:36.583
Yeah, a bit.

39:38.126 --> 39:39.502
Clean and serene
now, though.

39:39.627 --> 39:40.670
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:41.254 --> 39:42.714
So great
to see you again.

39:44.340 --> 39:46.342
JUSTIN: But she hadn't
seen me again...

39:48.177 --> 39:49.429
because the Lexie
| recognized

39:49.554 --> 39:51.264
from the seminars
was you.

39:51.931 --> 39:53.224
Undercover.

39:53.683 --> 39:55.143
Yeah.

39:55.268 --> 39:57.020
Are you going back
to Trinity?

39:57.770 --> 39:58.730
If | can.

39:59.981 --> 40:01.441
I'm sure you can.

40:01.608 --> 40:03.776
Just go to
registrations,

40:03.902 --> 40:06.029
say, "I'm
Lexie Mangan,

40:06.195 --> 40:08.656
"I- I'm back, bitches."
[ LAUGHS ]

40:08.781 --> 40:11.993
[ CHUCKLES ] Maybe not
the bitches bit.

40:12.118 --> 40:13.786
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:13.912 --> 40:15.622
Justin, the tattoo
on her wrist,

40:15.747 --> 40:16.706
the circle,

40:17.832 --> 40:18.750
what was that about?

40:21.502 --> 40:24.047
JUSTIN: She said, "Only
a madwoman or a genius

40:24.213 --> 40:25.715
"can draw a freehand circle.

40:26.966 --> 40:28.426
"Take your pick which one | am."

40:33.431 --> 40:35.683
| never wanted to leave
her in that cottage.

40:37.060 --> 40:38.603
Never.

40:38.770 --> 40:41.814
But suddenly,
everything was decided

40:41.940 --> 40:42.857
and cleaned up.

40:42.982 --> 40:44.150
Daniel.

40:45.193 --> 40:50.073
He said everything
would be all right.

40:53.284 --> 40:56.037
That we could all
go on like normal.

40:57.413 --> 40:59.082
But it never
was normal...

41:00.249 --> 41:01.334
and all right.

41:02.627 --> 41:04.671
[ DOOR OPENS ]

41:04.796 --> 41:06.756
Justin, | need to get you
all out of here.

41:07.340 --> 41:09.842
Daniel is planning
something.

41:10.009 --> 41:12.804
- [ DOOR CLOSES ] - Where did
he put his grandfather's gun?

41:12.929 --> 41:14.597
He said he put it
somewhere safe.

41:14.764 --> 41:18.267
[ STAMMERING ] | think maybe
he might have given it to Abby.

41:18.393 --> 41:20.603
He calls her
his safe place.

41:20.728 --> 41:22.438
DANIEL: And obviously,
he was a graduate.

41:25.108 --> 41:26.567
You feel better, Justin?

41:26.693 --> 41:28.152
Of course, he is.

41:28.277 --> 41:29.696
We're all
feeling better.

41:29.821 --> 41:32.156
In fact, this doesn't
need to get messy.

41:32.991 --> 41:34.200
No one needs to panic

41:34.325 --> 41:35.702
or leave the country.

41:35.827 --> 41:37.704
| mean, we were all just
trying to protect him.

41:38.371 --> 41:40.164
Seriously, you are
doing this now?

41:41.666 --> 41:42.542
Yes.

41:43.251 --> 41:45.294
I'm going with her.

41:45.420 --> 41:46.504
So, I'm tidying up.

41:46.671 --> 41:48.047
You're not gonna do it,
you never do.

41:49.424 --> 41:51.676
Itwas a
spur-of-the-moment thing

41:51.801 --> 41:54.512
and we just wanted
to protect Justin.

41:54.679 --> 41:55.722
He's vulnerable.

41:56.139 --> 41:57.306
JUSTIN: Daniel...

41:58.641 --> 42:00.309
Where's the key
for the back door?

42:01.853 --> 42:02.770
Somewhere.

42:13.740 --> 42:14.657
You can't go.

42:17.452 --> 42:18.745
| don't want you to.

42:21.122 --> 42:22.582
We stick together.

42:22.707 --> 42:24.876
That's the pledge we
all made to each other.

42:25.043 --> 42:26.419
You took an oath.

42:26.544 --> 42:27.628
You can't
break that now.

42:27.754 --> 42:29.047
It's just
something you say.

42:29.172 --> 42:30.423
- [ DISHES CLATTER ]
- No!

42:30.548 --> 42:32.550
No, it's not just
something | said!

42:32.675 --> 42:34.218
It's something
we said!

42:34.385 --> 42:36.345
We said that
and we meant it!

42:36.471 --> 42:37.930
You said those
words to me!

42:38.097 --> 42:39.515
Fucking said
that to me!

42:39.640 --> 42:41.476
We said them
to each other!

42:41.601 --> 42:43.144
The other gun,
the old revolver.

42:43.269 --> 42:44.228
Have you got it?

42:44.395 --> 42:45.605
You shut the fuck up!

42:45.730 --> 42:46.814
RAFE: What are you doing?

42:48.691 --> 42:49.984
You're not going
to shoot me.

42:50.068 --> 42:51.360
- DANIEL: No?
- No.

42:52.612 --> 42:53.696
You're gonna
shoot them.

42:54.405 --> 42:55.865
And then yourself.

42:56.407 --> 42:57.909
Four bodies
shot with my gun

42:58.076 --> 42:59.410
and me left
to deal with it.

43:01.537 --> 43:03.873
Why did you try and kill
that boy at school, Daniel?

43:04.874 --> 43:06.209
What had he done to you?

43:11.297 --> 43:12.131
[ WHIMPERING ]

43:24.310 --> 43:25.895
He didn't want to be
my friend anymore.

43:30.233 --> 43:31.317
Let him go.

43:31.484 --> 43:32.652
Let him go.
It can just be us.

43:32.819 --> 43:33.611
Just us two.

43:33.778 --> 43:34.779
Doesn't work
if it's just us two.

43:34.904 --> 43:36.155
Never did!

43:36.322 --> 43:37.573
ABBY: Daniel!

43:43.663 --> 43:44.789
Rafe!

43:44.914 --> 43:46.332
You crazy bastard!

43:49.252 --> 43:50.503
OFFICER 1: On your knees! Stop!

43:50.628 --> 43:51.170
- OFFICER 2: Stop!

43:51.295 --> 43:52.046
- OFFICER 1: Put your hands
in the air!

43:52.713 --> 43:54.132
OFFICER 3: Do not move!

43:54.257 --> 43:55.383
OFFICER 1: Do not move!

43:55.508 --> 43:57.135
FRANK: Don't
struggle, it'll hurt.

43:57.343 --> 43:58.136
On your knees.

43:58.261 --> 43:59.512
ABBY: Why did you come here?

43:59.637 --> 44:01.139
- We were happy until
you came here.

44:01.264 --> 44:01.931
- CASSIE: On the floor.

44:02.431 --> 44:03.975
- Abby, lie on the floor!
-[ GRUNTS ]

44:04.183 --> 44:05.476
Hands behind your back,
eyes closed.

44:05.601 --> 44:06.519
Don't get up
till you're told.

44:06.686 --> 44:08.187
Justin, keep
her still.

44:08.312 --> 44:09.814
- JUSTIN: Yeah.
- Daniel!

44:10.857 --> 44:12.358
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

44:15.403 --> 44:16.779
[ ABBY CRYING ]

44:22.743 --> 44:23.786
You lied.

44:24.370 --> 44:25.580
It's what | do.

44:27.707 --> 44:28.916
Drop the weapon.

44:29.375 --> 44:30.626
Drop it, Daniel.

44:32.086 --> 44:33.296
Drop it, Daniel!

44:42.221 --> 44:44.140
Imagine if you and Lexie
had met each other,

44:44.974 --> 44:45.975
face-to-face.

44:48.936 --> 44:49.854
Do you know what happens

44:50.855 --> 44:52.440
when doppelgangers
meet each other?

44:54.775 --> 44:55.985
The world ends.

45:03.951 --> 45:05.286
[ GUNSHOT]

45:05.411 --> 45:06.621
[ RINGING ]

45:11.751 --> 45:12.877
[ THUD ]

45:26.224 --> 45:27.308
[ DOG BARKING ]

45:27.433 --> 45:28.684
[ DISTANT SHOUTING ]

45:33.731 --> 45:35.608
OFFICER 1: Put your hands
above your head.

45:35.733 --> 45:37.193
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

45:37.318 --> 45:38.444
[ HELICOPTER WHIRRING ]

45:40.571 --> 45:43.783
RAFE: Shit, shit, shit.
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

45:45.076 --> 45:46.619
[ABBY SOBBING ]

45:50.248 --> 45:51.499
[ SOBBING CONTINUES ]

45:54.627 --> 45:56.212
[ WOMAN SPEAKING ON RADIO ]

45:56.379 --> 45:57.338
Cart over there
please, will you?

45:57.463 --> 45:58.673
Thank you.

46:02.510 --> 46:04.220
[ INDISTINCT CHATTER]

46:04.345 --> 46:05.638
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

46:09.308 --> 46:10.726
FRANK: | knew
something was wrong.

46:19.068 --> 46:20.111
They're not going
to Dublin.

46:20.236 --> 46:22.780
I'll process them
somewhere more discreet.

46:23.906 --> 46:25.074
Because
it's a mess.

46:25.199 --> 46:26.659
It's not that
much of a mess.

46:27.368 --> 46:29.203
Bit of a...

46:29.328 --> 46:32.498
creative spin for your report,
and it's a roaring success.

46:32.623 --> 46:34.125
| made a mistake.

46:35.418 --> 46:36.294
| was careless.

46:39.005 --> 46:41.299
| should have been more cautious
about what | drank, but...

46:41.757 --> 46:42.800
| wasn't.

46:42.925 --> 46:44.135
Well, no one
needs to know that.

46:45.761 --> 46:48.431
Creative spin,
Cass.

46:48.556 --> 46:51.392
Don't send in your report
until we've talked, okay?

46:51.517 --> 46:52.852
I'll get someone
to take you home.

46:58.065 --> 46:59.191
Good job,
by the way.

47:01.193 --> 47:02.445
Nerves of steel, man.

47:04.322 --> 47:05.239
Yeah, good job.

47:15.207 --> 47:16.959
[ TRUCK DRIVING AWAY ]

47:25.259 --> 47:26.218
YOUNG ADAM: Peter, Jamie.

47:28.637 --> 47:29.972
[ CHILDREN LAUGHING ]

47:30.181 --> 47:31.182
Peter?

47:31.724 --> 47:33.100
Where'd you go?

47:37.188 --> 47:38.522
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

47:41.359 --> 47:42.818
Where have you been?

47:42.985 --> 47:44.945
Come on. You're
always the last.

47:45.071 --> 47:46.238
Come on.

47:46.364 --> 47:47.990
[ FOOTSTEPS RECEDING ]

47:48.616 --> 47:49.700
[ DOOR OPENS ]

47:55.206 --> 47:56.499
[ PANTING ]

47:56.624 --> 47:57.500
Keep up, Adam!

47:57.625 --> 47:58.918
[ PANTING ]

48:02.338 --> 48:03.547
[ GLASS CRUNCHING |

48:04.548 --> 48:06.092
Run, Adam,
or they'll get you!

48:06.258 --> 48:07.510
Wait for me!

48:08.344 --> 48:09.428
You never wait!

48:09.762 --> 48:11.764
Peter? Jamie?

48:13.557 --> 48:15.893
[ MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO ]

48:17.353 --> 48:18.521
ROB: Wait.

48:19.355 --> 48:20.272
Peter!

48:20.898 --> 48:21.857
Jamie!

48:23.401 --> 48:24.568
Come back.

48:26.153 --> 48:28.406
Peter? Jamie?

48:29.240 --> 48:30.241
Jamie?

48:32.201 --> 48:33.327
Peter?

48:34.578 --> 48:35.996
Where are you?
Come back.

48:36.122 --> 48:37.081
Peter?

48:37.206 --> 48:38.833
Jesus Christ, son!
You nearly fell in.

48:38.958 --> 48:40.626
Come away, you
could have drowned.

48:40.751 --> 48:41.877
Come home.

48:42.002 --> 48:44.088
Come- come
home with me.

48:44.213 --> 48:46.799
Wake up, son!
For Christ's sake, wake up!

48:52.346 --> 48:53.931
[ LIGHTER FLICKS OPEN ]

48:58.519 --> 49:00.062
CLARE: You might have glass
in your feet.

49:01.647 --> 49:02.815
Need to
clean them.

49:04.483 --> 49:06.610
You should never have
gone back to Knocknaree.

49:08.946 --> 49:11.157
Telling people you were
dead in a car crash,

49:12.408 --> 49:14.243
out in the street,
shouting their names,

49:15.828 --> 49:18.164
and your clothes smell
of petrol and burning.

49:19.457 --> 49:20.332
What have you
been doing?

49:25.629 --> 49:26.964
What does Cassie
say about this?

49:31.760 --> 49:33.220
| don't know.
She's gone.

49:35.473 --> 49:36.599
Gone where?

49:39.310 --> 49:41.687
You've done to her
what you do to everyone.

49:44.440 --> 49:45.357
What do | do?

49:45.483 --> 49:46.650
You freeze them out.

49:47.693 --> 49:48.903
You go cold.

49:51.864 --> 49:53.032
| don't know
how it happens.

49:56.076 --> 49:58.746
| had this sweet,
loving little boy.

50:00.581 --> 50:02.875
Now you're this cold,
cold man.

50:05.085 --> 50:07.463
You don't know
how it happens?

50:07.588 --> 50:09.006
Even when your
dad was dying,

50:10.591 --> 50:12.259
and he wanted you
to take his hand

50:12.384 --> 50:13.260
and just hold it,

50:14.220 --> 50:15.763
hold it while he died,

50:16.805 --> 50:19.391
and you couldn't
even do that.

50:19.517 --> 50:20.851
And | don't
know you.

50:21.644 --> 50:23.437
| don't
recognize you.

50:24.230 --> 50:27.107
How could you not have
held your dad's hand?

50:27.233 --> 50:28.817
You put me

50:28.943 --> 50:32.071
in a fucking boarding school
in a different country.

50:32.780 --> 50:35.950
| didn't know
a single fucking soul

50:36.075 --> 50:38.285
and you left me there.

50:38.410 --> 50:40.871
You left me there
with strangers.

50:41.997 --> 50:44.416
How the fuck do you
expect me to be?

50:45.668 --> 50:46.961
[ SNIFFLING ]

50:51.799 --> 50:53.551
You sound like
an Irish man.

51:01.850 --> 51:04.562
We wanted you
to have routine.

51:07.189 --> 51:08.899
We didn't know
what to do.

51:12.111 --> 51:13.946
| missed my friends.

51:15.281 --> 51:16.532
Oh, | missed them.

51:16.824 --> 51:19.410
Why do you still
worship those kids?

51:20.369 --> 51:21.787
They were vicious
to you.

51:24.915 --> 51:26.417
- No, they weren't.
- Vicious.

51:27.918 --> 51:29.712
| hated you
playing with them.

51:29.837 --> 51:31.547
Your dad said it was
just kids being kids

51:31.672 --> 51:32.840
and | should cut
the apron strings,

51:32.965 --> 51:35.926
but | felt sick watching
you go off with them.

51:36.051 --> 51:37.970
You never liked them
because you're a snob.

51:38.137 --> 51:41.932
| didn't like them
because they were bad kids!

51:42.099 --> 51:45.060
Cruel kids, taunting
you for being little,

51:45.185 --> 51:46.812
always running off
and leaving you on your own

51:47.021 --> 51:48.981
in those
bloody woods.

51:49.106 --> 51:51.358
Laughing at you, and
you'd come home crying.

51:51.525 --> 51:54.945
- No, | didn't.
- I'd beg you to stay home.

51:55.070 --> 51:58.490
| tried everything to stop
you, but you still went,

51:58.657 --> 52:00.868
following them
like a little puppy.

52:00.993 --> 52:02.494
Why would you
tell me this?

52:02.703 --> 52:05.414
Why would you say this?
| don't understand.

52:06.832 --> 52:07.916
Because...

52:10.210 --> 52:12.588
You've remembered
us all wrong.

52:13.422 --> 52:16.216
You're trapped in it.

52:18.344 --> 52:20.804
And | don't want
you to be trapped.

52:22.890 --> 52:25.893
| don't want your life
to be ruined, Adam.

52:32.358 --> 52:33.734
Don't call me that.

52:52.086 --> 52:53.504
[ WATER RUNNING ]

53:09.061 --> 53:10.646
ANSWERING MACHINE:
First new message.

53:10.813 --> 53:13.607
ROB: [ OVER PHONE ]
Cassie, it's Rob. Come back.

53:13.732 --> 53:15.943
| have something
| want to tell you.

53:24.118 --> 53:25.369
[ DOOR OPENS ]

53:34.461 --> 53:36.338
[ EXHALES ]

53:36.463 --> 53:39.883
The caravan's freezing,
so we've come back.

53:41.176 --> 53:42.511
Place is a pigsty.

53:43.512 --> 53:44.430
A disgrace.

53:45.973 --> 53:47.099
You should be ashamed.

53:49.309 --> 53:52.020
We should have rung
to warn you, Daddy. I'm sorry.

53:53.063 --> 53:55.065
I'll soon have
this sorted out.

53:55.190 --> 53:56.984
[ DISHES CLATTERING ]

54:07.995 --> 54:09.037
You look funny.

54:19.757 --> 54:21.133
[ BIRDS CAWING ]

54:45.073 --> 54:46.200
[ TICKING ]

54:48.076 --> 54:49.453
[ TICKING ]

54:52.414 --> 54:53.916
We shouldn't
have seen that.

54:54.041 --> 54:56.543
PETER: But we did.
The dirty gits.

54:57.836 --> 55:00.464
We can use it against 'em.
Have some fun.

55:02.633 --> 55:04.593
[ SHOUTING ] We saw
your hairy arseholes!

55:04.718 --> 55:07.554
We saw you doing it,
you dirty beasts!

55:07.679 --> 55:09.181
YOUNG ADAM: Don't.

55:09.306 --> 55:10.724
Look at you.
Wanna be at home

55:10.849 --> 55:12.476
watching your top twenties
with your mam?

55:12.601 --> 55:13.477
You're no fun.

55:13.602 --> 55:15.103
That's your
problem, Adam.

55:15.229 --> 55:16.396
- You're no fun.
- [ ECHOES ] You're no fun.

55:18.106 --> 55:19.566
Such a waste
of skin.

55:41.880 --> 55:43.715
- [ ENGINE WHIRRING ]
- [ INDISTINCT CHATTERING ]

55:46.593 --> 55:47.636
[ MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

55:51.223 --> 55:53.517
MARK: Can't leave the
place alone, huh?

55:55.018 --> 55:55.978
Do you want one?

55:56.103 --> 55:57.312
Look like you
could do with it.

55:58.105 --> 55:59.231
Yeah, thanks.

56:01.733 --> 56:02.734
Tanks on the lawn.

56:04.027 --> 56:05.404
Can't wait
to get started.

56:07.155 --> 56:09.074
That's probably the last of
those we'll be doing for you.

56:09.992 --> 56:11.034
ROB: Right.

56:14.246 --> 56:15.581
Did you find what
you were looking for?

56:16.415 --> 56:17.749
No.

56:17.875 --> 56:18.792
Nor did I.

56:19.751 --> 56:21.879
At least we tried.

56:22.045 --> 56:23.505
Gotta count for
something, hasn't it?

56:23.630 --> 56:24.548
Trying?

56:28.010 --> 56:29.803
They're a bit stale.

56:29.928 --> 56:31.054
Fine if you
dunk it, though.

56:32.556 --> 56:34.141
COOPER: Advanced
digestive process.

56:34.266 --> 56:36.310
So, eaten a good
five hours before death.

56:36.435 --> 56:38.103
And a chocolate
biscuit.

56:38.228 --> 56:39.521
Initial digestive
process.

56:40.397 --> 56:41.565
Whose were these, Mark?

56:41.732 --> 56:43.859
Biscuits? Damien
always brought them.

56:44.860 --> 56:45.986
Damien?

56:46.111 --> 56:47.154
Always eating,
that boy.

56:47.279 --> 56:49.197
Hollow legs.
Why?

56:53.368 --> 56:54.661
ROB: Mrs. Donnelly
is S0 sick,

56:54.786 --> 56:56.121
| don't want her house
being taken over

56:56.246 --> 56:57.623
until we have to.

57:06.131 --> 57:08.175
[ HINGES CREAKING ]

57:10.135 --> 57:11.345
Why didn't | look?

57:12.262 --> 57:14.431
This is how
he moved the body.

57:14.556 --> 57:16.642
I didn't even look to
see if there was a car.

57:18.560 --> 57:19.728
Do you want me
to start in here?

57:23.065 --> 57:24.066
Inside.

57:27.152 --> 57:29.404
MRS. DONNELLY: | know
you have a job to do,

57:29.529 --> 57:30.822
but you'll find
nothing here.

57:31.865 --> 57:33.742
It's a mistake.

57:33.867 --> 57:35.702
Damien's the best boy
in the world, isn't he?

57:37.788 --> 57:39.790
We'll do our best
not to disturb you.

57:41.333 --> 57:42.459
[ DOOR CREAKING ]

57:50.175 --> 57:52.386
Her clothes had been
washed and dried.

57:52.636 --> 57:54.179
She had been
kept somewhere.

57:56.390 --> 57:58.308
[ MACHINE WHIRRING ]

58:00.519 --> 58:02.688
I'm thinking,
